>Roger</i>) is impossible to tell."],"variants":[{"name":"Duckett","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): from the Middle English personal name <i>Duket</i>. This may sometimes have been an early Middle English pet form of an Old English <i>Ducc(a)</i>, but was more often a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>, especially in Yorkshire (see   Duke  ). <i>Marmaduke</i> itself is from Irish <i>Maol Maedóc</i> ‘servant of Maedóc’, <i>Maedóc</i> being the name of prominent Irish saints of the 6th and 7th centuries."]}]},{"name":"Andrew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":1,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Andrew Doggett was born in 1454, in Groton, Suffolk, England, his father, Sir Andrew Doget Docket, was 40 and his mother, Elizabeth Middleton, was 42. He married Katherine Duckett in 1481, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 6 November 1484, in Grayrigg, Westmorland, England, at the age of 30, and was buried in Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England."},"et":{"1454–6 November 1484":"1454–6. november 1484","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1461–Female":"1461–Surnud","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1414–1484":"1414–1484","1412–1485":"1412–1485","11 November 1484":"11. november 1484","6 November 1484":"6. november 1484","1 Jan 1442":"1. jaanuar 1442","4 Nov 1484":"4. november 1484","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1481":"1481","1414":"1414","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1485":"1485","1 January 1481":"1. jaanuar 1481","1526":"1526","Grayrigg, Westmorland, England":"Grayrigg, Westmorland, England","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Groton, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, England","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England"},"fi":{"1454–6 November 1484":"1454–6. marraskuuta 1484","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1461–Female":"1461–Kuollut","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1414–1484":"1414–1484","1412–1485":"1412–1485","11 November 1484":"11. marraskuuta 1484","6 November 1484":"6. marraskuuta 1484","1 Jan 1442":"1. tammikuuta 1442","4 Nov 1484":"4. marraskuuta 1484","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1481":"1481","1414":"1414","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1485":"1485","1 January 1481":"1. tammikuuta 1481","1526":"1526","Grayrigg, Westmorland, England":"Grayrigg, Westmorland, England","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Groton, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, England","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England"},"fr":{"1454–6 November 1484":"1454–6 novembre 1484","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1461–Fema